Peru Stocks: Austral, Maple Energy, Pomalca, Relapasa, Siderperu

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-25T21:35:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/peru-stocks-austral-maple-energy-pomalca-relapasa-siderperu.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index dropped 3.3 percent to 18,176.55.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 3.1 percent to 2,504.07.  Industrial stocks slumped after a weekend poll showed
former military rebel Ollanta Humala leading rival Keiko Fujimori ahead of June 5 presidential elections, said Miguel Pancorvo, the head trader at Lima-based brokerage Compass SAB.
Humala has pledged to impose a windfall tax on mining companies
and renegotiate trade accords with nations like the U.S. and
 Canada .  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker, plunged 8.8
percent to 1.14 soles. Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA
(POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo, fell 8.2 percent to 45
centimos. Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll
Seafood ASA, dropped 7.1 percent to 26 centimos. Corp. Aceros
Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, fell 6.5
percent to 2.30 soles.  Fuel refiners dropped after crude futures in New York fell.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, plummeted 8.1 percent to 68
cents. Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 6.1 percent to 1.34 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
